CARTO HTML for maps (Part #1):

  • This weeks assignment will consist of two parts. Part #1 features working with HTML syntax within CARTO map[s]. Both legend and pop-up map elements can be modified extensively to tailor the performance of a CARTO map. Utilize the following video guide to orient towards effective revision/modification of both map elements - legends and pop-ups:

  • To start, navigate to your CARTO account and either develop a new map based on skills/procedures youve learned in the previous 3 classes; or alter an existing map created in CARTO in previous classes.

  • Next, edit the legend to add a link (or links) to your datasource(s) utilized in the map. Utilize the Class 4 HTML for CARTO pop-ups and legends video tutorial for legend revisions.

  • Following the legend edit[s], Make a change to the HTML for the pop-ups for your map. This can be as simple as adding <strong> elements to emphasize some text, or you could link to other pages or show images. Again, utilize Class 4 HTML for CARTO pop-ups and legends video tutorial for pop-up revisions.

HTML page development (Part #2)

  • In this second assignment component, you will reference your CARTO map from Part #1 above utilizing the embed iframe element approach covered in Lecture 4 Demonstration.

  • To start, navigate to your Glitch account and initiate a new hello-website:

Initiate new hello-website

  • Next, either revise the default hello-website > index.html, or clear the html code therein and start with a blank slate using a standard HTML template (HTML5 Template), one of which is available as Class 4 Demonstration Code:

Access code via View Page Source from Class 4 Demonstration Code

Note: if you would like to do your HTML development in your destkop editor (VS Code), that is a valid/encouraged option. Once you complete your development, you can then simply copy > paste to your Glitch hello-website > index.html. Keep in mind that Glitch logs project hours of which there is a limit per month in the free tier. Make sure to close your browser to the site when you are not actively working in Glitch to keep your project hours to a minimum.

  • In your HTML index.html development, include at least the following additions/revisions:
  1. Embed the Carto map from Part 1 in the page as an iframe
  2. Add a Title to the page
  3. Add a short synopsis of your iframe map
  4. Add at least one image
  5. Add at least one link

  • Remember to access the HTML Cheatsheet to assist your HTML development for the 5 page components noted above, as well as any further development that you chose to do.

  • If you are working primarily in Glitch, remember to format your final html. You can do this step via the Prettier tab at the top of your html document:

Glitch offers a built-in code formatting tool

  2. A valid link to the CARTO map itself. This is the link option following Publish titled Get the link (left side).
  3. Valid links to the Glitch project developed in Part #2 - both the code link and the live site links.
